{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487379"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:08:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:08:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"334"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/334"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.62,0.11,0.05,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"334"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101510"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/334"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-10-07T15:03:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-08T11:25:02+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2021-06-23T05:52:23+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-01 14:05:12"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"334"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9435"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83949"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"26"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"318"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"3343"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"5595"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"12917"},{"type":"tags","id":"12921"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2828"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2848"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35187"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37067"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83949"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101510","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/101510"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 61-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of worsening left knee pain. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He smokes 20 cigarettes per day and drinks two to four cans of beer daily. He is diagnosed with osteoarthritis and subsequently undergoes an elective total left knee replacement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn day three post-surgery, the nursing staff report that he has become confused and distressed. He is expressing a desire to leave the hospital. On examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 130/min, blood pressure 90/40 mmHg, respiratory rate 25/min, SpO2 80% on room air, and temperature 38.7\u00b0C.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["500 mL crystalloid fluid intravenously as a bolus","Supplemental oxygen by face mask","Urgent medical emergency team review","Intravenous broad spectrum antibiotics","1 L of 0.9% sodium chloride fluid intravenously as a bolus"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has developed acute post-operative deterioration with confusion, hypoxia, hypotension, tachycardia and fever. While multiple issues need addressing, management should follow the systematic ABCDE (Airway, Breathing, Circulation, Disability, Exposure) approach to the critically unwell patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupplemental oxygen by face mask\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first step as breathing problems take priority over circulation in the primary survey. The patient\u0027s oxygen saturation of 80% requires immediate correction before addressing other issues. Hypoxia may be contributing to confusion. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E500 mL crystalloid fluid\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003E1 L of 0.9% sodium chloride\u003C/strong\u003E would be appropriate subsequent steps to address the hypotension, but only after ensuring adequate oxygenation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUrgent medical emergency team review \u003C/strong\u003Ewould be appropriate given the concerning vital signs, but the first priority is to commence oxygen therapy rather than waiting for the team to arrive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous broad spectrum antibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E would be appropriate if sepsis is suspected, which is possible given the fever and post-operative setting. However, immediate resuscitation takes priority.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe differential diagnosis in this scenario includes post-operative pneumonia, pulmonary embolism, or sepsis from a wound infection. After initial stabilisation, urgent investigations including chest imaging, ECG, blood cultures, and assessment of the surgical site would be required.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A haemodynamically unstable patient should be assessed and managed in a stepwise manner using the primary survey ABCDE approach.","Airway and breathing issues take priority over circulation in the primary survey.","Post-operative confusion with hypoxia, tachycardia, and fever requires urgent assessment for complications such as pulmonary embolism or pneumonia."],"references":["Miller MO. Evaluation and management of delirium in hospitalized older patients. Am Fam Physician. 2008;78(11):1265-70. Available at: https://www.aafp.org/pubs/afp/issues/2008/1201/p1265.html","Smith D, Bowden T. Using the ABCDE approach to assess the deteriorating patient. Nurs Stand. 2017;32(14):51-63. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29185642/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83949"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"334"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83949","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/83949"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-02T12:58:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-02T13:10:24+09:30","number":11,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-05-02T13:09:46+09:30","plagiarismScore":13.3,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-334-11.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250928%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250928T173813Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=56fa8c8f205d9a0d99daf207bf371fd709138a72eba07871e704dc7fb307cc5b"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"334"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101510"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"738"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"26","links":{"self